{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5452fc0c-db7f-45f8-b145-424ca4c5a38f","content":"The project doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but I can tell you exactly what to configure. To publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org, add these properties to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Required for dotnet tools -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet package metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n\n  <!-- Must be Exe for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — makes it installable via `dotnet tool install`\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — required for stdio transport\n\n**Publish steps:**\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Users install with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install --global MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server   # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWant me to apply these changes to your `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f131503-17fd-48f5-a6bb-945689ed6604","outputTokens":470,"requestId":"3843:2A9B4:6FCC4C8:782EC63:6A03D02C"},"id":"43717ae3-4908-4b89-9a7a-de935912f3f8","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:13:24.766Z","parentId":"e5f504e8-5424-4629-b5bf-e829bd821a62"}
